Project stack:
- Laravel 8
- PHP 8
- Livewire 2
- Alpine.js 3
- TailwindCSS 3

General rules:
- Follow Laravel conventions
- Write clean and maintainable code
- Prefer readability over clever code
- Keep components small and reusable
- Avoid duplicated code
- Use meaningful variable and method names
- Prefer Eloquent relationships over raw queries
- Avoid N+1 queries
- Use eager loading when appropriate
- Keep business logic out of Blade files
- Prefer service/action classes for complex logic

Livewire rules:
- Use Livewire 2 syntax only
- Keep Livewire components focused and modular
- Avoid excessive public properties
- Use proper loading states
- Minimize unnecessary re-renders
- Prefer computed/accessor style methods when appropriate

Frontend rules:
- All frontend UI must follow docs/design-system.pdf
- Use iOS-inspired admin design
- UI must be:
  - clean
  - airy
  - subtle
  - consistent

Design system requirements:
- Use rounded-xl for inputs/buttons
- Use rounded-2xl for cards/modals
- Use soft shadows only
- Use spacious spacing
- Use slate color palette
- Use primary color system from design-system.pdf
- Use hover states for web interactions
- Avoid cramped layouts
- Avoid heavy borders
- Avoid heavy shadows
- Avoid inconsistent spacing
- Avoid inconsistent input styles

Tailwind rules:
- Prefer Tailwind utility classes
- Avoid inline styles
- Reuse common UI patterns
- Keep class structures readable

Blade rules:
- Prefer reusable Blade partials/components
- Keep Blade templates clean
- Avoid large monolithic Blade files

Table/UI rules:
- Tables should be responsive and readable
- Use subtle hover states
- Prioritize content readability
- Maintain consistent spacing and alignment

Code style:
- Prefer explicit and readable code
- Avoid over-engineering
- Keep naming consistent across the project

Architecture:
- Respect existing project architecture
- Do not rename core structures unless requested
- Preserve backward compatibility when possible